---
import Expand from "@/components/ui/Expand.astro";
---

<div class="mb-8">
	<Expand title="Privacy Policy">
		<div slot="content">
			<p>
				I <b><em>do not track you</em></b>, I <b><em>do not run analytics</em></b>, I <b>
					<em>do not set cookies</em>
				</b>
			</p>
			<p>
				I <b><em>do write four values to your browser's localStorage</em></b>: your <b>
					<em>light/dark theme preference</em>
				</b>, whether to <b><em>match your device theme</em></b>, whether you've chosen to <b
					><em>pause the blinking cursor effect</em></b
				>, and your <b><em>8-bit avatar customisation</em></b> (if you've used the avatar builder). These persist across visits
				by design so you shouldn't have to reconfigure your preferences every time you open the site.
			</p>
			<p>
				The <b><em>only data I receive from you</em></b>, is that <b><em>which you freely give me</em></b> through the <b>
					<em>email</em>
				</b> or <b><em>guestbook forms</em></b>.
			</p>
			<p>
				Guestbook submissions are stored in a self-hosted <a
					href="https://turso.tech"
					target="_blank"
					rel="noopener noreferrer">
					Turso
				</a> database (libSQL). Spam is filtered using a honeypot field and content pattern detection. No third-party services
				process your data. Should you want a copy or would like me to delete anything you sent me;
			</p>
			<p>
				Contact me directly on <i class="icon-envelope-at"></i>: <a class="icon" href="mailto:alex@alexmbugua.me">
					alex@alexmbugua.me
				</a>
			</p>
			<p>
				Raise an issue in the <i class="icon-github"></i> repo <a
					class="icon"
					href="https://github.com/asce1062/asce1062/issues"
					target="_blank"
					rel="noopener noreferrer">
					asce1062/issues
				</a>
			</p>
			<p>Or whichever way you prefer to ask for this - I will happily oblige.</p>
		</div>
	</Expand>
</div>
